      "text": [
        " رِوَايَةِ حَرِيزٍ عَنْ أَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ قَالَ: «اَلصَّائِمُ إِذَا خَافَ عَلَى عَيْنَيْهِ مِنَ اَلرَّمَدِ أَفْطَرَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1945 - In the narration of Hariz from Abu Abdullah (as), he said:\n\"A fasting person, if they fear harm to their eyes due to an eye infection, may break their fast.\""
        ]
      }
